{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:18:11.995Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Exploring Login Components**\n\nI've examined `/app/admin/login/page.tsx` and it also uses `<SecureLogin defaultRole=\"Administrator\" />`. I'm starting to visualize a premium login component, `SecureLogin.tsx`, with a focus on an enterprise-grade design. I'm brainstorming the layout, envisioning a modern split-screen design for desktops and a centered layout for mobile. This will have a beautiful login interface and a clean, secure flow. The interface will include a GFF AI Brand header, multi-tab auth selector, and forms.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:18:13.638Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Mock Identity Enclave**\n\nI'm now focusing on integrating simulated identity options within the login flow. I'm thinking of incorporating \"Continue with Okta\" and \"SAML 2.0 Identity Hub\" options. I'm envisioning a \"FRONTEND ONLY GATEWAY - Zero-Trust Local Sandbox\" label to emphasize the local simulation. A premium \"Authenticate & Connect\" button will drive interaction. I am also working on a \"Zero-Trust Identity Enclave\" panel with simulated user roles, auto-populating login credentials, to make testing easy.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:18:15.578Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining UI Constitution**\n\nI'm now detailing visual elements for the UI. I'm focusing on a premium 2026 enterprise design with a calm, spacious layout and subtle background animations, ensuring responsiveness and accessibility. I'm prioritizing proper aria attributes, keyboard navigation, tabIndex, and visible focus rings. I've sketched a multi-tab interaction for authentication, including Security Key/Password, OTP, and SSO options. Each tab will have placeholder components for validation or mock authentication.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:18:17.832Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Mock Interactions**\n\nNow, I'm integrating interactive mock data population within the \"Zero-Trust Identity Enclave.\" The \"Enclave Sandbox Profile Selector\" dynamically updates the active form fields based on the chosen role.  For example, selecting \"Password Auth\" populates mock email and password fields. \"OTP\" fills mock OTP code fields, and \"SSO\" highlights the Okta/Azure button as authorized. This makes for a great local role preview.\n\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
