rom this structured data, which allows for quick role selection. I'm focusing on ensuring these roles will aid simulated testing.\n\n\n**Simulating Scan Transition**\n\nI'm now integrating a login scan simulation, enhancing the \"Authenticate Enclave\" button's transition. It will include a 900ms scanning animation with 4 key steps displayed, such as \"Establishing zero-trust gateway handshake.\" I'm upgrading the UI to a premium decrypting overlay with sleek SVG lines and counters. This makes the simulation truly exciting!\n\n\n**Constructing Input Options**\n\nI'm now detailing the password authentication tab's UI. I've designed three premium pill buttons for auth type selection (\"Password,\" \"Enterprise SSO,\" \"One-Time OTP\") on a black rounded track. Under the \"Password\" tab, I've designed modern, premium email and password input fields with focus effects. I'm also including a \"Remember Me\" checkbox, and \"Forgot Password?\" link. I'm starting SSO interaction design, like the simulated modal and scanning simulation on button click.\n\n\n**Refining OTP Input**\n\nI'm now refining the One-Time OTP tab's input design. I've focused on creating six custom input slots that dynamically auto-focus and support keyboard movement, paste, and backspace. I'm also adding a \"Resend Code\" counter for a premium touch. The \"Authenticate & Establish Connection\" button now has a bright blue glow on hover, scale transition, and focus rings.\n\n\n\n"}}
