the modal opens correctly after the authentication processes. I'm also reviewing the appearance and layout of each button, and ensuring the text is correctly displayed.\n\n\n**Optimizing Button States**\n\nI'm now focusing on optimizing the state of the form submission button, specifically its responsiveness during the authentication process. I'm scrutinizing the click handlers to ensure that they disable the button appropriately, preventing multiple submissions and providing a clear visual indication of progress.\n\n\n**Refining Layout Elements**\n\nI'm now refining the layout elements of the \"Enclave Switcher\" section. I'm focusing on the positioning of elements within the container to enhance visual clarity and user experience. I'm prioritizing the visual hierarchy of the \"Development Only\" label, headline, and descriptive text. I am also adjusting their spacing for optimal readability and impact.\n\n\n**Optimizing Role Selection**\n\nI'm now focusing on optimizing the role selection functionality, specifically the rendering of the role list and its interactive elements. I'm focusing on ensuring smooth selection, and accessibility for a seamless user experience. I am checking the styles applied to the selected item and its visual contrast.\n\nI am also making sure that the list displays correctly across different screen sizes.\n\n\n**Evaluating Role Rendering**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the component that renders the roles list, focusing on the visual display and interactivity. I'm prioritizing the visual distinction of the selected role. Additionally, I'm checking the responsive design of the list, to ensure optimal display across screen sizes and accessibility.\n\n\n\n**Analyzing Role Elements**\n\nI'm now carefully analyzing the role selection visual elements. I'm focusing on the ID section's display, along with the dynamic color change of the shield element, to ensure proper visual representation based on client roles. The line's animation also needs to be smooth.\n\n\n**Refining Element Styling**\n\nI'm now refining the styling of individual elements within the role section. Specifically, I'm adjusting the animations to work with responsive design, and ensuring the `strokeDasharray` is properly calculated for the line animation. I'm focusing on the `isClientRole`'s application of the appropriate colors to the `Cpu` element, along with the `PORTAL` and `ADMIN` display.\n\n\n**Evaluating Role UI**\n\nI'm now carefully evaluating the UI elements within the role section, starting with the `<Fingerprint />` icon. I'm reviewing the button's click behavior, and also the visual states. I'll test the button to see if the colors and animation accurately reflect the `isClientRole` state.\n\n\n\n**Assessing Animation Effects**\n\nI'm now focusing on the pulse animation within the button component, analyzing its visual impact and ensuring it aligns with the overall UI/UX. I'm focusing on its timing and smoothness.\n\n\n**Evaluating Modal Interaction**\n\nI'm now focusing on the modal component interaction, specifically the behavior of the \"close\" and \"Operations Support\" buttons. I want to make sure the modal is closed and opens the support modal in the correct sequence. The current implementation is now working as intended.\n\n\n\n**Assessing Handshake Logic**\n\nI'm now analyzing the recent addition of system help and operations details within the modal. I'm reviewing their alignment within the content, and ensuring the buttons' behavior is as expected. I'm also going to check the overall interaction flow within the modals.\n\n\n**Refining SSO Federation**\n\nI'm now focusing on the integration and visual representation of Single Sign-On (SSO) federation within the SecureLogin form. I'm prioritizing the clarity of the connection process for the user, specifically the \"connecting SSO federation\" indicator. I'm reviewing the visual states of the message to ensure it aligns with the overall UI.\n\n\n"}}
